  "prompt": "What is the best site to download songs?",
  "response": "The best site to download songs can vary based on your preferences and needs. Here are some popular and reputable options:\n\n1. **Amazon Music**: Offers a vast library of songs for purchase and download. Amazon Prime members also have access to millions of tracks via Prime Music.\n   \n2. **iTunes/Apple Music**: Apple\u2019s music platform offers a large catalogue of songs for purchase and download, and Apple Music subscribers have access to an extensive streaming library.\n\n3. **Google Play Music**: Although transitioning to YouTube Music, it remains a platform where you can purchase and download tracks.\n\n4. **Spotify**: Primarily a streaming service, but with the premium subscription, you can download songs for offline listening.\n\n5. **Bandcamp**: Great for independent artists and niche genres. Users can support artists directly by purchasing and downloading their music.\n\n6. **SoundCloud**: Some artists offer free downloads of their tracks, and premium subscribers can download songs for offline listening.\n\nAlways ensure that you use legitimate and legal sites to download music to support the artists and avoid any legal issues.",
